frameDefinitions: This frame contains general words for Individuals, i.e. humans, whose specific acts or general behavior is evaluated against standards of morality or rightness.
An Agent resolves an outstanding Problem by finding its solution, explanation, answer, etc.
The words in this frame involve an Undesirable_event which affects the Patient negatively.
A Wrongdoer engages in a Misdeed.
A Perpetrator (generally intentionally) commits a Crime, i.e. does something not permitted by the laws of society.
A person or group, the Authority, believes that another person, the Suspect is a participant in a criminal Incident.
frameExamples: Columbus: Was he a Hero or a <t>Villain</t>?
As it turns out, putting all of my eggs in one basket completely <t>solved</t> all of my problems.
The first <t>calamity</t> was a disastrous trade war with Holland.
You have <t>sinned</t> for the last time, Stephen!
They <t>perpetrated</t> a felony by substituting a lie for negotiations.
The police <t>suspect</t> Noah Rogers of aiding the robbery last night at Shop-n-drive.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Person</fen> is the human being.
The <fen>Agent</fen> finds the solution or explanation to the outstanding mystery or <fen>Problem</fen>.
The <fen>Problem</fen> is the predicament or mystery that is resolved.
The <fen>Cause</fen> is the non-Agentive event or state of affairs that brings about the resolution of the <fen>Problem</fen>.
This role indicates the <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Problem</fen> is resolved.
This role indicates the location at which the <fen>Problem</fen> is resolved.
The undesirable event which occurs.
The entity that experiences the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen>.
When the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> occurs.
Where the <fen>Undesirable_Event</fen> takes place.
This is the person whose <fen>Misdeed</fen> is being judged with respect to its morality.
The assessment of the <fen>Wrongdoer</fen> is based on his or her <fen>Misdeed</fen>.
The time at which a <fen>Misdeed</fen> is performed.
The location where a <fen>Misdeed</fen> occurs.
The individual that commits a <fen>Crime</fen>.
When the <fen>Crime</fen> was committed.
The location where the <fen>Crime</fen> occurs.
The <fen>Authority</fen> is the group or person who suspects the <fen>Suspect</fen> of criminal activity.
The <fen>Suspect</fen> is the target of the <fen>Authority</fen>'s suspicion.
The (typically criminal) <fen>Incident</fen> in which the <fen>Suspect</fen> is suspected of being involved.
When the suspecting takes place.
listRoleExamples: If <fex>we</fex> have not been able to resolve a problem to your satisfaction, please email us.
Likewise, once the students worked through <fex>the problem</fex> and obtained their results, their next assignment would be to publish these to the web.
First, <fex>the Tripartite Agreement of 1979</fex> actually solved the only significant friction between the two countries.
A group of international scientists solved the fundamental particle hierarchy question <fex>at an underground accelerator</fex>.
An <fex>environmental</fex> disaster is just what we need.
The misdeeds <fex>of the previous evening</fex> were all forgotten now.
Sexual peccadilloes <fex>in the White House</fex> are one thing, lying before Congress quite another.
How can <fex>he</fex> commit treason against the King of England in a foreign country , if he is not English?
A murder perpetrated <fex>at 1:08AM this morning</fex> was not investigated until noon today.
We have jurisdiction over crimes committed <fex>in Woodside County</fex>.
Jakobson was placed under suspicion <fex>last week</fex> .
